narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned to speak better, since the class was small, and sharpened up on my French grammar skills.
This course provided a deeper understanding of French syntax and semantics through a greater analysis of French texts.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The strengths of this class are how immersive it is. The weakness is how the course material is laid out - L'Etranger is the most challenging and should come at the end of the course

Strength: Pierre was the best professor ever 
weakness: there's only one Pierre and he's not teaching again
I feel like it sometimes can go a little too fast for me, and if one struggles in 120 or 121, it would be hard to pick up 130
This course is well-organized and the teaching staff is highly dedicated to making sure students understand the material and feel confident when speaking the language.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: It helps you satisfy the language requirement and it is well taught. However, it takes a lot of time to do well in the course.
I would recommend this course to a student who is interested in improving both their ability to speak French and their overall understanding of French grammar.
